node.title: Travellers test positive to Omicron COVID-19 strain after arriving in Sydney from southern Africa
node.alt: travellers at the airport holding onto a baggage trolley
node.description: NSW Health confirmsÂ two returned travellers have tested positive for the new Omicron COVID-19 variant in Sydney.
node.content: ["NSW Health has confirmed two returned travellers have tested positive for the new Omicron COVID-19 variant in Sydney.", "The two positive cases are in isolation in the Special Health Accommodation.\u00a0", "Both people, who are fully vaccinated, arrived in Sydney from southern Africa on Saturday, November 27.", "They are among\u00a014 people who arrived on Qatar Airways QR908, Doha to Sydney, about 7pm.", "The remaining 12 passengers from southern Africa are undertaking 14 days of hotel quarantine, also in the Special Health Accommodation.", "About 260 passengers and air crew on the flight are considered close contacts and have been directed to isolate.\u00a0", "Yesterday evening, NSW Health changed its advice for international travellers returning to Sydney as a precaution to\u00a0stem the spread of the new Omicron B.1.1.529 variant.\u00a0", "Anyone arriving in the state from the\u00a0nine impacted southern African countries \u2014 South Africa, Lesotho, Botswana, Zimbabwe, Mozambique, Namibia, Eswatini, Malawi, and the Seychelles \u2014 is now required to go into hotel quarantine for 14 days.\u00a0", "More to come."]
